<br>
Lots of experienced players starting over here, living for the thrill of questing, roleplaying and the occasional GM event<br>
<br>
/rude Legends<br>
<br>
Not much twinking that I can see, if it appears that way it is primarily a gift from a higher level guild member to a younger. When I see someone with special quest gear all I think is, wow that scrapper has put a lot of time into getting that, grats to them. Of course there are many people who have re rolled characters and started over, trying to get their heart behind roleplaying the character, as opposed to, I wanna be a warrior because they are the most needed high end character or something. These people commonly have handed down equipment to their new persona to wear or sell.<br>
<br>
The challenges of quests at the appropriate level as opposed to &quot;farmers&quot; and nearly vacant zones have given a special feel to this server. Not everyone has the same Uber-item_003. When you get that first bear hide quest armor, it feels great, because a person of similar level isn't running up wearing Sebilis gear and telling you the stats and how you need to get such and such if you are to be worth anything. Some people still level like mad, as is their want, but they don't throw it in your face.<br>
<br>
If you re frequenting the Qeynos area, I will likely bump into you at some time, look forward to it  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 <p>Minuet the Talechaser<br>
The enchanting half-elf bard of Qeynos. <br>

Circle of Sisters

