<br>
There's nothing wrong with it. Most people on this server would rather give away the stuff then destroy it, thus you get your twinks. Especially as people move on from planar gear to better stuff (planes usually being some of the first &quot;high end&quot; gear guilds get before moving on to greater challenges).<br>
<br>
And of course folks that had planar gear before SoL came out. There is TONS of gear that is better than planar in SoL. As an example my first planar raids on this server resulted in me passing on several loots, just cuz I already had better. When I get even better gear, I am not going to mothball my old gear in the bank (bank space much to valuable) and I am certainly not gonna destroy it. I'm gonna give it away or sell it to someone (assuming ewveryone in my guild has the same or better).<br>
<br>
Its because of this that I dont think we can say we will see less twinking on FV. With there only being one character per account I think we'll see more twinking as more and more people start doing planes and other challenges. There are already two guilds that are what you might call &quot;uber&quot; and I beleive a thrid guild has recently asked for a turn in the draco rotation. So possibly three &quot;uber&quot; guilds on FV now. In time a fouth will appear, I think Clan Were (spelling?) has several folks over 50 now so we may see them trying planes and stuff soon too. Anyway.. /rambling off.<br>
 <p>Kzan Verto<BR>
Giver of "da juice" (tm)
